Python Snippets Categories
--------------------------

If you want to add a snippet to the archive, please add the SNIPPET metadata
in the comments at the top of the file.

This will make it easier for programs to browse and make use of your snippet.

One piece of metadata is SNIPPET_CATEGORIES. E.g.:

    # [SNIPPET_CATEGORIES: PyGTK]

When adding a snippet please try to use one of the following categories if suitable:

    Application Indicator   Application indicator examples.
    bzrlib                  Bazaar source control system Python module.
    Cairo		            Cairo drawing examples
    Clutter                 Clutter toolkit examples.
    csv                     csv Python module, reading and writing CSV files
    dbus        	    dbus messaging system
    doctest		    The doctest module.
    DesktopCouch            DesktopCouch examples.
    email		    email related snippets
    feedparser	            Parsing RSS feeds.
    gconf                   GNOME configuration manager snippets.
    gobject		            The gobject library, part of GNOME.
    Gstreamer               Python-gstreamer examples.
    Gwibber	                Gwibber microblogging tool
    inspect                 inspecting modules
    launchpadlib            Samples using launchpadlib.
    Notify OSD              Notify OSD examples.
    os			            os Python module OS related snippets.
    OpenOffice.org	    Snippets the handle OpenOffice.org files.
    PyGTK                   PyGTK widget and framework examples.
    PyGTKSourceView         PyGTKSourceView widget and framework examples.
    Python Core             Examples that demonstrate core features in the Python language.
    Python VTE              Snippets using the VTE widget for GTK.
    PyTurtle                Turtle Python module examples.
    PyKDE4                  KDE Python bindings.
    PyQt4                   PyQt4 widget examples
    Patterns                Design pattern examples.
    Regular Expression      Samples using Regular Expressions
    smtplib		    sending mail with smtplib
    socket                  Networking socket examples
    tarfile		            Samples using tarfile.
    Testing                 Examples using Python test frameworks.
    threading               Threading examples
    twitter		    Microblog with the twitter module. The gwibber module can also do this.
    unittest		    The unittest module for unit testing.
    xml			    xml module snippets.
    Zeitgeist               Samples on how to use Zeitgeist.

If you need another category, add it to your snippet and to the list above. Thanks!
